# YouTube to Apple Music Bridge — Project Overview

You are working on a **monorepo** with two products:

## 1. Chrome Extension (`src/`)
Detects music videos on YouTube and opens them in Apple Music (native app).

- **Stack**: TypeScript, React, Tailwind CSS, Vite
- **Architecture**: Content scripts → Background service worker → Popup UI
- **Key integrations**: iTunes Search API, OpenAI (optional), Supabase community DB
- **Build**: `npm run build` → load `dist/` in Chrome

## 2. Website (`website/`)
Audiophile-focused song search — find any song on Apple Music from a YouTube link or song name.

- **Stack**: Next.js 16, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- **Key integrations**: iTunes Search API, Supabase community DB, Vercel Analytics
- **Build**: `cd website && npm run build`
- **Deploy**: Vercel (auto-deploys from main)

## Shared Infrastructure

- **Supabase**: Community song database with RLS + RPCs (`find_mapping`, `add_mapping`, `confirm_mapping`, `find_mapping_by_apple_music`)
- **iTunes API**: Free, no key needed. Used for song search and metadata enrichment.
- **Apple Music URLs**: Web (`https://music.apple.com/us/song/{id}`) and native (`itmss://music.apple.com/us/song/{id}`)

## File Structure
```
src/                    # Chrome extension source
├── popup/              # React popup UI
├── background/         # Service worker
├── content/            # YouTube content scripts
├── utils/              # Shared utilities (Apple Music, AI, cache)
└── types/              # TypeScript definitions
website/                # Next.js website (separate from extension build)
├── src/app/            # Pages and API routes
└── src/lib/            # Supabase, iTunes, YouTube utilities
```

## Critical Rules
1. **NEVER** auto-close Chrome alerts/prompts — user has full control
2. **NEVER** use setTimeout to close tabs
3. Use **ONLY** `itmss://` scheme for native Apple Music app opening
4. Store cache confirmation data **immediately** — no delays
5. Clear `currentVideoData` on YouTube URL changes to prevent stale data
6. Extension users must NOT download website code (separate build targets)

## Detailed Rules
See `.cursor/rules/` for file-specific patterns:
- `chrome-extension.mdc` — Chrome API, message passing, user control
- `youtube-detection.mdc` — Content scripts, DOM access, title cleaning
- `caching-system.mdc` — Cache confirmation, background script patterns
- `ai-integration.mdc` — OpenAI fallback patterns
- `react-typescript.mdc` — Component standards, TypeScript, styling
- `website.mdc` — Next.js, Tailwind v4 quirks, Supabase, SEO
